Q9:  How to view some countries’ interference in China’s legislative issues?

A: These are gross interference in China’s internal affairs. We hope they can fully respect China’s sovereignty, and maintain an objective and fair position on issues related to Hong Kong.

see👉 https://t.co/iYvOWCDSUw

Q8:  Will the legislation violate the “Sino-British Joint Declaration”?

A: The “Sino-British Joint Declaration” only addresses the returning of HK.  After the return, the legal basis for the Chinese government to govern HK is China's Constitution and the Basic Law of HK.

see👉 https://t.co/J2O7Ir6WtT

Q7:  Will the legislation affect Hong Kong's foreign enterprises?

A: The legislation will not affect the legitimate rights and interests of foreign enterprises in Hong Kong at all. On the contrary, they will benefit from a more stable HK.

see👉 https://t.co/0G8cTOhhj7

legacy.full_text: Former #HongKong SAR chief prosecutor defends #NationalSecurityLegislation https://t.co/T16qts5ufx

The former HKSAR chief prosecutor said: since present situation in HK is intolerable, and local government of HKSAR is unable to enact the national security law according to Art. 23 of the Basic Law, the Central Government had really no option but to enact the law by itself.

Q6:  Is the legislation eroding the judicial autonomy of Hong Kong?

A:  The judicial autonomy of Hong Kong is ensured by Basic Law. National security legislation will not affect the Hong Kong courts' independent exercise of its judicial power.

see👉 https://t.co/mZYw0lJrr5

Q5:  Is the legislation against the“one country, two systems”principle？

A:  Maintaining national security is the core of "one country, two systems." The institutional arrangement by the NPC firmly upholds it and ensures that it moves in the right direction.

see👉 https://t.co/d1jqYbRRAw

Q4:  Will the legislation affect HK residents' rights and freedoms?

A:  Targeting only acts of secession, subversion and terrorism, as well as external interference in the HKSAR's internal affairs. The legislation will not affect the rights and freedoms HK citizens. 

see👉 https://t.co/10cONGIWrn

Q3:  How will the legislation be promoted?

A: It will be promoted by "decision + law". First,  the NPC has made the decision to enact the legislation on May 28. Then, the NPC will formulate laws which will be included in Annex III of HK Basic Law and implemented by HK.

see👉 https://t.co/7erz9SslZP
